task.summary: Default task
Skip ConstructLastRowBuildingTrait if no cards are available (filter Senators).

Cards are revealed (=set as available in gamestate value VALUE_AVAILABLE_CARDS) at the end of the player turn (in NextPlayerTurnTrait.php) or at the start of a new age (NextAgeTrait.php) to prevent this information being available too soon during mid-turn decisions. The exception is DiscardAvailableCardTrait (Conspiracy "Turn of Events"), whose enterState and actions reveal cards as well.

Cards are revealed (=set as available in gamestate value VALUE_AVAILABLE_CARDS) at the end of the player turn (in NextPlayerTurnTrait.php) or at the start of a new age (NextAgeTrait.php) to prevent this information being available too soon during mid-turn decisions. The exception is DiscardAvailableCardTrait (Conspiracy "Turn of Events"), whose enterState and actions reveal cards as well.

In Agora (or maybe Pantheon for the future), the draftpool of Age I should be visible during the Wonder Selection. This update accomodates that, including some graphical tweakes to make the middle column content as compact and tight as possible. Update Wonder Selection round title more consistently so it gets set when refreshing in other sub states as well (conspire, placeinfluence etc).
Player loses Victory Points when a progress token (with VPs) is locked away by Conspiracy Obscurantism. Centralized losing of victory points in Item's deconstruct method.
Fixed player name being wrong when active player backs into a Military Token.
Conspiracy Sabotage: return Age card to discard, not the box.
Fixed bookmarks and added workspace.xml
Fixed Conspiracy Treason animation problem for inactive player.
Check if at least 1 of the Conspiracy's actions can have an effect - don't allow a Conspiracy to trigger if it has no possible effect.
Bugfix getRows for Age 0: Return empty age structure with at least 1 row, which gets checked by getLastRowBuildings
Removed all revealCards from args function. There should be no database mutations in args function, which likely caused the deadlocks. Added preEnterState mechanic.
Removed hacky temporary change of VALUE_CURRENT_AGE global variable, likely contributing to the deadlock issue.
Fix "Senate Chamber" translatability, and Grey/Brown/Blue/Yellow in ChooseOpponentBuildingTrait.php
Only update VALUE_AVAILABLE_CARDS if value is different to what is in the database, in an attempt to reduce deadlocks.
CHOOSE_PROGRESS_TOKEN_FROM_BOX_NAME would crash the javascript when triggered through Conspiracy Espionage (10) and the Wonder 6 was not on the table.
shouldSkipTriggerUnpreparedConspiracy can now actually skip in case of Curia Julia, not just say it's skipping in the log.
Conspiracy's isUsefulToTrigger did not check for Coercion's 2nd action.
Fixed setAvailableCardIds current and new values Added admin function to force available card recalculation on a bug report by bug report basis (hopefully no longer needed with above fix.

Don't check for usefulness of Conspiracies when preparing the Conspiracy (resulting in grayed out Prepare a Conspiracy button). Don't scale down Wonders for inactive player during chooseConspireRemnantPosition.
Improve order of log messages for lost control of senate chamber & military step
Replaced SevenWondersDuel with SevenWondersDuelPantheon
Added material and game setup for Pantheon
Bugfix #28711. With Agora, the conflict pawn can go backwards, so the winner isn't always the active player.
#1 player Pistol Star felt that the 3 picked progress tokens were not truly random. For his peace of mind and for the outside change that this is actually the case, add a shuffle here.
Made "Conspiracy deck" translatable. Made buildingTypeTranslatable marked as i18n.
Added Pantheon tokens spritesheet WIP. Added some Pantheon expansion checks
Changed font Cafetaria-Black's implementation to comply with Adobe's policy.
Image updates for Pantheon

Mythology token deck implementation.
